vue-components.name: BAlert
vue-components.description: Provide contextual feedback messages for typical user actions with the handful of available and flexible alert messages.

props.name: show
props.description: When set, shows the alert. Set to a number (seconds) to show and automatically dismiss the alert after the number of seconds has elapsed

props.name: dismissLabel
props.description: Value for the 'aria-label' attribute on the dismiss button

props.name: dismissible
props.description: When set, enables the dismiss close button

props.name: fade
props.description: When set to `true`, enables the fade animation/transition on the component

props.name: variant
props.description: Applies one of the Bootstrap theme color variants to the component

events.name: dismiss-count-down
events.description: When prop show is a number, this event emits every second on countdown

arguments.name: dismissCountDown
arguments.description: Time remaining to dismissed

events.name: dismissed
events.description: Alert dismissed either via the dismiss close button or when the dismiss countdown has expired

events.name: input
events.description: Used to update the v-model show value

arguments.name: show
arguments.description: Boolean state of alert, or Number for current countdown value

slots.name: dismiss
slots.description: Content for the dismiss button

vue-components.name: BAvatar
vue-components.description: Avatars are typically used to display a user profile as a picture, an icon, or short text.

props.name: activeClass
props.description: <router-link> prop: Configure the active CSS class applied when the link is active. Typically you will want to set this to class name 'active'

props.name: alt
props.description: Value to place in the 'alt' attribute for image and icon avatars

props.name: append
props.description: <router-link> prop: Setting append prop always appends the relative path to the current path

props.name: ariaLabel
props.description: Sets the value of `aria-label` attribute on the rendered element

props.name: badge
props.description: When `true` shows an empty badge on the avatar, alternatively set to a string for content in the badge

props.name: badgeLeft
props.description: When `true` places the badge at the left instead of the right

props.name: badgeOffset
props.description: CSS length to offset the badge. Positive values move the badge inwards, while negative values move the badge outwards

props.name: badgeTop
props.description: When `true` places the badge at the top instead of the bottom

props.name: badgeVariant
props.description: Applies one of the Bootstrap theme color variants to the badge

props.name: button
props.description: When set to `true`, renders the avatar as a button

props.name: buttonType
props.description: Type of button to render (i.e. `button`, `submit`, `reset`). Has no effect if prop button is not set

props.name: disabled
props.description: When set to `true`, disables the component's functionality and places it in a disabled state

props.name: exact
props.description: <router-link> prop: The default active class matching behavior is inclusive match. Setting this prop forces the mode to exactly match the route

props.name: exactActiveClass
props.description: <router-link> prop: Configure the active CSS class applied when the link is active with exact match. Typically you will want to set this to class name 'active'

props.name: exactPath
props.description: <router-link> prop: Allows matching only using the path section of the url, effectively ignoring the query and the hash sections

props.name: exactPathActiveClass
props.description: <router-link> prop: Configure the active CSS class applied when the link is active with exact path match. Typically you will want to set this to class name 'active'

props.name: href
props.description: <b-link> prop: Denotes the target URL of the link for standard a links

props.name: icon
props.description: Icon name to use for the avatar. Must be all lowercase. Defaults to `person-fill` if `text` or `src` props not provided

props.name: noPrefetch
props.description: <nuxt-link> prop: To improve the responsiveness of your Nuxt.js applications, when the link will be displayed within the viewport, Nuxt.js will automatically prefetch the code splitted page. Setting `no-prefetch` will disabled this feature for the specific link

props.name: prefetch
props.description: <nuxt-link> prop: To improve the responsiveness of your Nuxt.js applications, when the link will be displayed within the viewport, Nuxt.js will automatically prefetch the code splitted page. Setting `prefetch` to `true` or `false` will overwrite the default value of `router.prefetchLinks`

props.name: rel
props.description: <b-link> prop: Sets the `rel` attribute on the rendered link

props.name: replace
props.description: <router-link> prop: Setting the replace prop will call `router.replace()` instead of `router.push()` when clicked, so the navigation will not leave a history record

props.name: rounded
props.description: Specifies the type of rounding to apply to the avatar. The `square` prop takes precedence. Refer to the documentation for details

props.name: routerComponentName
props.description: <b-link> prop: BootstrapVue auto detects between `<router-link>` and `<nuxt-link>`. In cases where you want to use a 3rd party link component based on `<router-link>`, set this prop to the component name. e.g. set it to 'g-link' if you are using Gridsome (note only `<router-link>` specific props are passed to the component)

props.name: size
props.description: Size of the avatar. Refer to the documentation for details

props.name: square
props.description: Disables rounding of the avatar, rending the avatar with square corners

props.name: src
props.description: Image URL to use for the avatar

props.name: target
props.description: <b-link> prop: Sets the `target` attribute on the rendered link

props.name: text
props.description: Text to place in the avatar

props.name: to
props.description: <router-link> prop: Denotes the target route of the link. When clicked, the value of the to prop will be passed to `router.push()` internally, so the value can be either a string or a Location descriptor object

props.name: variant
props.description: Applies one of the Bootstrap theme color variants to the component

events.name: click
events.description: Emitted when the avatar is clicked when rendered as a button or link. Not emitted otherwise

arguments.name: event
arguments.description: Native Event object

events.name: img-error
events.description: Emitted if an image `src` is provided and the image fails to load

arguments.name: event
arguments.description: Native Event object

slots.name: badge
slots.description: Content to place in the avatars optional badge. Overrides the `badge` prop

slots.name: default
slots.description: Content to place in the avatar. Overrides props `text`, `src`, and `icon-name`

vue-components.name: BDd
vue-components.description:
Dropdowns are toggleable, contextual overlays for displaying lists of links and actions in a dropdown menu format.

*Alias for BDropdown*

props.name: id
props.description: Used to set the `id` attribute on the rendered content, and used as the base to generate any additional element IDs as needed

props.name: boundary
props.description: The boundary constraint of the menu: 'scrollParent', 'window', 'viewport', or a reference to an HTMLElement

props.name: disabled
props.description: When set to `true`, disables the component's functionality and places it in a disabled state

props.name: dropleft
props.description: When set, positions the menu to the left of the button

props.name: dropright
props.description: When set, positions the menu to the right of the button

props.name: dropup
props.description: When set, positions the menu on the top of the button

props.name: noFlip
props.description: Prevent the menu from auto flipping positions

props.name: offset
props.description: Specify the number of pixels to shift the menu by. Negative values supported

props.name: popperOpts
props.description: Additional configuration to pass to Popper.js

props.name: right
props.description: Align the right edge of the menu with the right of the button

props.name: block
props.description: Renders a 100% width toggle button (expands to the width of its parent container)

props.name: html
props.description: HTML string to place in the toggle button, or in the split button is split mode

props.name: lazy
props.description: When set, will only mount the menu content into the DOM when the menu is open

props.name: menuClass
props.description: CSS class (or classes) to add to the menu container

props.name: noCaret
props.description: Hide the caret indicator on the toggle button

props.name: role
props.description: Sets the ARIA attribute `role` to a specific value

props.name: size
props.description: Set the size of the component's appearance. 'sm', 'md' (default), or 'lg'

props.name: split
props.description: When set, renders a split button dropdown

props.name: splitButtonType
props.description: Value to place in the 'type' attribute on the split button: 'button', 'submit', 'reset'

props.name: splitClass
props.description: CSS class (or classes) to add to the split button

props.name: splitHref
props.description: Denotes the target URL of the link for the split button

props.name: splitTo
props.description: <router-link> prop: Denotes the target route of the split button. When clicked, the value of the to prop will be passed to router.push() internally, so the value can be either a string or a Location descriptor object

props.name: splitVariant
props.description: Applies one of the Bootstrap theme color variants to the split button. Defaults to the 'variant' prop value

props.name: text
props.description: Text to place in the toggle button, or in the split button is split mode

props.name: toggleAttrs
props.description: Additional attributes to apply to the toggle button

props.name: toggleClass
props.description: CSS class (or classes) to add to the toggle button

props.name: toggleTag
props.description: Specify the HTML tag to render instead of the default tag

props.name: toggleText
props.description: ARIA label (sr-only) to set on the toggle when in split mode

props.name: variant
props.description: Applies one of the Bootstrap theme color variants to the component

events.name: bv::dropdown::hide
events.description: Emitted on $root just before dropdown is hidden. Cancelable

arguments.name: bvEvent
arguments.description: BvEvent object. Call bvEvent.preventDefault() to cancel hide

events.name: bv::dropdown::show
events.description: Emitted on $root just before dropdown is shown. Cancelable

arguments.name: bvEvent
arguments.description: BvEvent object. Call bvEvent.preventDefault() to cancel show

events.name: click
events.description: Emitted when split button is clicked in split mode

arguments.name: event
arguments.description: Native click event object

events.name: hidden
events.description: Emitted when dropdown is hidden

events.name: hide
events.description: Emitted just before dropdown is hidden. Cancelable

arguments.name: bvEvent
arguments.description: BvEvent object. Call bvEvent.preventDefault() to cancel hide

events.name: show
events.description: Emitted just before dropdown is shown. Cancelable

arguments.name: bvEvent
arguments.description: BvEvent object. Call bvEvent.preventDefault() to cancel show

events.name: shown
events.description: Emitted when dropdown is shown

events.name: toggle
events.description: Emitted when toggle button is clicked

slots.name: button-content
slots.description: Can be used to implement custom text with icons and more styling

slots.name: default
slots.description: Optionally scoped default slot for dropdown menu content

vue-properties.name: hide
vue-properties.description: Can be used to close the dropdown menu. Accepts an optional boolean argument, which if true returns focus to the toggle button

vue-components.name: BDropdownItem
vue-components.description: Dropdowns are toggleable, contextual overlays for displaying lists of links and actions in a dropdown menu format.

props.name: active
props.description: When set to `true`, places the component in the active state with active styling

props.name: activeClass
props.description: <router-link> prop: Configure the active CSS class applied when the link is active. Typically you will want to set this to class name 'active'

props.name: append
props.description: <router-link> prop: Setting append prop always appends the relative path to the current path

props.name: disabled
props.description: When set to `true`, disables the component's functionality and places it in a disabled state

props.name: exact
props.description: <router-link> prop: The default active class matching behavior is inclusive match. Setting this prop forces the mode to exactly match the route

props.name: exactActiveClass
props.description: <router-link> prop: Configure the active CSS class applied when the link is active with exact match. Typically you will want to set this to class name 'active'

props.name: exactPath
props.description: <router-link> prop: Allows matching only using the path section of the url, effectively ignoring the query and the hash sections

props.name: exactPathActiveClass
props.description: <router-link> prop: Configure the active CSS class applied when the link is active with exact path match. Typically you will want to set this to class name 'active'

props.name: href
props.description: <b-link> prop: Denotes the target URL of the link for standard a links

props.name: linkClass
props.description: Class or classes to apply to the inner link element

props.name: noPrefetch
props.description: <nuxt-link> prop: To improve the responsiveness of your Nuxt.js applications, when the link will be displayed within the viewport, Nuxt.js will automatically prefetch the code splitted page. Setting `no-prefetch` will disabled this feature for the specific link

props.name: prefetch
props.description: <nuxt-link> prop: To improve the responsiveness of your Nuxt.js applications, when the link will be displayed within the viewport, Nuxt.js will automatically prefetch the code splitted page. Setting `prefetch` to `true` or `false` will overwrite the default value of `router.prefetchLinks`

props.name: rel
props.description: <b-link> prop: Sets the `rel` attribute on the rendered link

props.name: replace
props.description: <router-link> prop: Setting the replace prop will call `router.replace()` instead of `router.push()` when clicked, so the navigation will not leave a history record

props.name: routerComponentName
props.description: <b-link> prop: BootstrapVue auto detects between `<router-link>` and `<nuxt-link>`. In cases where you want to use a 3rd party link component based on `<router-link>`, set this prop to the component name. e.g. set it to 'g-link' if you are using Gridsome (note only `<router-link>` specific props are passed to the component)

props.name: target
props.description: <b-link> prop: Sets the `target` attribute on the rendered link

props.name: to
props.description: <router-link> prop: Denotes the target route of the link. When clicked, the value of the to prop will be passed to `router.push()` internally, so the value can be either a string or a Location descriptor object

props.name: variant
props.description: Applies one of the Bootstrap theme color variants to the component

events.name: click
events.description: Emitted when item is clicked

arguments.name: mouseEvent
arguments.description: Native click event object

slots.name: default
slots.description: Content to place in the dropdown item

vue-components.name: BFormDatepicker
vue-components.description: BootstrapVue custom date picker input form control, which provides full WAI-ARIA accessibility (a11y) and supports internationalization (i18n).

props.name: id
props.description: Used to set the `id` attribute on the rendered content, and used as the base to generate any additional element IDs as needed

props.name: value
props.description: Initially selected date value. Accepts either a `YYYY-MM-DD` string or a `Date` object

props.name: ariaControls
props.description: If this component controls another component or element, set this to the ID of the controlled component or element

props.name: boundary
props.description: The boundary constraint of the menu: `'scrollParent'`, `'window'`, `'viewport'`, or a reference to an `HTMLElement`

props.name: buttonOnly
props.description: Renders the datepicker as a dropdown button instead of a form-control

props.name: buttonVariant
props.description: The button variant to use when in `button-only` mode. Has no effect if prop `button-only` is not set

props.name: calendarWidth
props.description: Sets the width of the calendar dropdown (see the `b-calendar` prop `width` for details)

props.name: closeButton
props.description: When set, shows the optional close button

props.name: closeButtonVariant
props.description: Button variant to use for the optional `close` button

props.name: dark
props.description: When set, gives the popup calendar dialog a dark background

props.name: dateDisabledFn
props.description: Set to a function reference which returns `true` if the date is disabled, or `false` if the date should be enabled. See documentation for details

props.name: dateFormatOptions
props.description: Format object for displayed text string that is passed to `Intl.DateTimeFormat`

props.name: dateInfoFn
props.description: Set to a function reference which returns a class (string), or classes (array of strings) to apply to the date cell. See calendar documentation for details. Passed through to the child calendar component

props.name: direction
props.description: Set to the string 'rtl' or 'ltr' to explicitly force the calendar to render in right-to-left or left-ro-right (respectively) mode. Defaults to the resolved locale's directionality

props.name: disabled
props.description: Places the calendar in a non-interactive disabled state

props.name: dropleft
props.description: When set, positions the menu to the left of the button

props.name: dropright
props.description: When set, positions the menu to the right of the button

props.name: dropup
props.description: When set, positions the menu on the top of the button

props.name: form
props.description: ID of the form that the form control belongs to. Sets the `form` attribute on the control

props.name: headerTag
props.description: Specify the HTML tag to render instead of the default tag for the header

props.name: hideHeader
props.description: When `true`, visually hides the selected date header

props.name: initialDate
props.description: When a `value` is not specified, sets the initial calendar month date that will be presented to the user. Accepts a value in `YYYY-MM-DD` format or a `Date` object. Defaults to the current date (or min or max if the current date is out of range)

props.name: labelCalendar
props.description: Value of the `aria-label` and `role-description` attributes applied to the calendar grid

props.name: labelCloseButton
props.description: Content for the optional `Close` button

props.name: labelCurrentMonth
props.description: Value of the `aria-label` and `title` attributes on the `Current Month` navigation button

props.name: labelHelp
props.default: "Use cursor keys to navigate calendar dates"
props.description: Help text that appears at the bottom of the calendar grid

props.name: labelNav
props.description: Value of the `aria-label` attribute on to the calendar navigation button wrapper

props.name: labelNextDecade
props.description: Value of the `aria-label` and `title` attributes on the optional `Next Decade` navigation button

props.name: labelNextMonth
props.description: Value of the `aria-label` and `title` attributes on the `Next Month` navigation button

props.name: labelNextYear
props.description: Value of the `aria-label` and `title` attributes on the `Next Year` navigation button

props.name: labelNoDateSelected
props.description: Label to use when no date is currently selected

props.name: labelPrevDecade
props.description: Value of the `aria-label` and `title` attributes on the optional `Previous Decade` navigation button

props.name: labelPrevMonth
props.description: Value of the `aria-label` and `title` attributes on the `Previous Month` navigation button

props.name: labelPrevYear
props.description: Value of the `aria-label` and `title` attributes on the `Previous Year` navigation button

props.name: labelResetButton
props.description: Content for the optional `Reset` button

props.name: labelSelected
props.description: Value of the `aria-label` attribute set on the calendar grid date button that is selected

props.name: labelToday
props.description: Value of the `aria-label` attribute for the calendar grid date button to signify that the date is today's date

props.name: labelTodayButton
props.description: Content for the optional `Select today` button

props.name: locale
props.description: Locale (or locales) for the calendar to use. When passing an array of locales, the order of the locales is from most preferred to least preferred

props.name: max
props.description: The maximum date the calendar will show

props.name: menuClass
props.description: Class (or classes) to apply to to popup menu wrapper

props.name: min
props.description: The minimum date the calendar will show

props.name: name
props.description: Sets the value of the `name` attribute on the form control

props.name: navButtonVariant
props.description: Theme color variant to use for the navigation buttons

props.name: noCloseOnSelect
props.description: Disables closing the popup date picker when a date is clicked/selected

props.name: noFlip
props.description: Prevent the menu from auto flipping positions

props.name: noHighlightToday
props.description: Disabled the highlighting of todays date in the calendar

props.name: offset
props.description: Specify the number of pixels to shift the menu by. Negative values supported

props.name: placeholder
props.description: Text so show in the form control when no date is selected. Defaults to the `label-no-date-selected` prop value

props.name: popperOpts
props.description: Additional configuration to pass to Popper.js

props.name: readonly
props.description: Places the calendar in an interactive readonly state. Disables updating the v-model, while still allowing date navigation

props.name: required
props.description: When set, adds the `aria-required="true"` attribute on the component. Required validation needs to be handled by your application

props.name: resetButton
props.description: When set, shows the optional `reset` button

props.name: resetButtonVariant
props.description: Button variant to use for the optional `reset` button

props.name: resetValue
props.description: When the optional `reset` button is clicked, the selected date will be set to this value. Default is to clear the selected value

props.name: right
props.description: Align the right edge of the menu with the right of the button

props.name: selectedVariant
props.description: Theme color variant to use for the selected date button

props.name: showDecadeNav
props.description: When `true`, shows the +/- decade navigation buttons

props.name: size
props.description: Set the size of the component's appearance. 'sm', 'md' (default), or 'lg'

props.name: startWeekday
props.description: Day of week to start the calendar. `0` for Sunday, `1` for Monday, `6` for Saturday, etc.

props.name: state
props.description: Controls the validation state appearance of the component. `true` for valid, `false` for invalid, or `null` for no validation state

props.name: todayButton
props.description: When set, shows the optional `select today` button

props.name: todayButtonVariant
props.description: Button variant to use for the optional `select today` button

props.name: todayVariant
props.description: Theme color variant to use for highlighting todays date button. Defaults to the `selectedVariant` prop

props.name: valueAsDate
props.description: Returns a `Date` object for the v-model instead of a `YYYY-MM-DD` string

props.name: weekdayHeaderFormat
props.description: Format to use for the calendar weekday headings. Possible values are `long`, `short` (default), or `narrow`

events.name: context
events.description: `b-calendar` context event. Emitted when the user changes the active date via date navigation buttons or cursor control

arguments.name: context
arguments.description: The `b-calendar` context object. See the `b-calendar` documentaion for details

events.name: hidden
events.description: Emitted when the picker popup has hidden

events.name: input
events.description: Emitted when updating the v-model

arguments.name: date
arguments.description: Either a string in the format of `YYYY-MM-DD` or a `Date` object (if `value-as-date` prop is `true`)

events.name: shown
events.description: Emitted when the picker popup has shown

slots.name: button-content
slots.description: Content to place in the datepicker's icon button

vue-properties.name: isHovered
vue-properties.description: `true` if the component is hovered

vue-properties.name: hasFocus
vue-properties.description: `true` if the datepicker icon button has focus

vue-properties.name: state
vue-properties.description: The value of the `state` prop. `true` (valid), `false` (invalid), or `null`

vue-properties.name: open
vue-properties.description: The visibility state of the popup. `true` if the popup is visible and `false` if not

slots.name: nav-next-decade
slots.description: Used to place custom content in the next decade navigation button

vue-properties.name: isRTL
vue-properties.description: Will be `true` if the date navigation bar is rendered right to left

slots.name: nav-next-month
slots.description: Used to place custom content in the next month navigation button

vue-properties.name: isRTL
vue-properties.description: Will be `true` if the date navigation bar is rendered right to left

slots.name: nav-next-year
slots.description: Used to place custom content in the next year navigation button

vue-properties.name: isRTL
vue-properties.description: Will be `true` if the date navigation bar is rendered right to left

slots.name: nav-prev-decade
slots.description: Used to place custom content in the previous decade navigation button

vue-properties.name: isRTL
vue-properties.description: Will be `true` if the date navigation bar is rendered right to left

slots.name: nav-prev-month
slots.description: Used to place custom content in the previous month navigation button

vue-properties.name: isRTL
vue-properties.description: Will be `true` if the date navigation bar is rendered right to left

slots.name: nav-prev-year
slots.description: Used to place custom content in the previous year navigation button

vue-properties.name: isRTL
vue-properties.description: Will be `true` if the date navigation bar is rendered right to left

slots.name: nav-this-month
slots.description: Used to place custom content in the this month/day navigation button

vue-properties.name: isRTL
vue-properties.description: Will be `true` if the date navigation bar is rendered right to left

props.name: plain

props.name: accept

props.name: directory

props.name: noDrop

arguments.name: file

slots.description: Placeholder content, when no files selected. Defaults to `placeholder` prop value

props.name: id
props.description: Used to set the `id` attribute on the rendered content, and used as the base to generate any additional element IDs as needed

props.name: value
props.description: Array of current tags. This is the v-model

props.description: When set to `true`, attempts to auto-focus the control when it is mounted, or re-activated when in a keep-alive. Does not set the `autofocus` attribute on the control

props.name: disabled
props.description: When set to `true`, disables the component's functionality and places it in a disabled state

props.name: form
props.description: ID of the form that the form control belongs to. Sets the `form` attribute on the control

props.name: name
props.description: Sets the value of the 'name' attribute on the form control. When set, creates a hidden input for each tag

props.name: required
props.description: Adds the `required` attribute to the form control

props.name: size
props.description: Set the size of the component's appearance. 'sm', 'md' (default), or 'lg'

props.name: state
props.description: Controls the validation state appearance of the component. `true` for valid, `false` for invalid, or `null` for no validation state

props.name: addButtonText
props.description: Text for the built in 'Add' button. Slot `add-button-text' takes precedence

props.name: addButtonVariant
props.description: Applies one of the Bootstrap theme color variants to the 'Add' button

props.name: addOnChange
props.description: When set, enables adding the tag on the input's 'change' event

props.name: duplicateTagText
props.description: The message when duplicate tags are detected. Set to an empty string to disable the message

props.name: feedbackAriaLive
props.description: Value to use for the `aria-live` attribute on the feedback text

props.name: ignoreInputFocusSelector
props.description: Ignore certain elements from the click to focus input routine, specified by css selector(s)

props.name: inputAttrs
props.description: Additional attributes to apply to the new tag input element

props.name: inputClass
props.description: Class (or classes) to apply to the new tag input element

props.name: inputId
props.description: ID to apply to the new tag input element. If not provided, a unique ID will be auto generated

props.name: inputType
props.description: Specifies the type of input to use: 'text', 'email', 'tel', 'url', or 'number'. Default is 'text'

props.name: invalidTagText
props.description: The error message when invalid tags are detected. Set to an empty string to disable the message

props.name: limit
props.description: The maximum amount of tags that can be added. The limit can still be exceeded if manipulated outside of the component

props.name: limitTagsText
props.description: The message when the limit is reached. Set to an empty string to disable the message

props.name: noAddOnEnter
props.description: When set, disables adding the tag on the input's 'keydown.enter' event

props.name: noOuterFocus
props.description: When set, disables the focus styling of the component root element

props.name: noTagRemove
props.description: When set, the tags will not have a remove button

props.name: placeholder
props.description: Sets the 'placeholder' attribute value on the form control

props.name: removeOnDelete
props.description: When set, enables removal of last tag in tags when user presses delete or backspace and the input is empty

props.name: separator
props.description: Separator character(s) that will trigger a tag to be created

props.name: tagClass
props.description: Class (or classes) to apply to the tags

props.name: tagPills
props.description: Makes the built in tags have a pill appearance

props.name: tagRemoveLabel
props.description: The value of the 'aria-label' attribute on the remove button in the tag

props.name: tagRemovedLabel
props.description: Label for the aria-live region that announces removed tag(s) to screen reader users

props.name: tagValidator
props.description: Optional tag validator method. Passed a single argument of tag being added. Should return 'true' if the tag passes validation, or 'false' if the tag cannot be added

props.name: tagVariant
props.description: Applies one of the Bootstrap theme color variants to the tags

vue-components.name: BFormTimepicker
vue-components.description: BootstrapVue custom time picker input form control, which provides full WAI-ARIA accessibility (a11y) and supports internationalization (i18n).

props.name: id
props.description: Used to set the `id` attribute on the rendered content, and used as the base to generate any additional element IDs as needed

props.name: value
props.description: Initially selected time value. Accepts a `HH:mm:ss` string. Valid value ranges from `00:00:00` to `23:59:59`

props.name: ariaLabelledby
props.description: The ID of the element that provides a label for this component. Used as the value for the `aria-labelledby` attribute

props.name: boundary
props.description: The boundary constraint of the menu: `'scrollParent'`, `'window'`, `'viewport'`, or a reference to an `HTMLElement`

props.name: buttonOnly
props.description: Renders the datepicker as a dropdown button instead of a form-control

props.name: buttonVariant
props.description: The button variant to use when in `button-only` mode. Has no effect if prop `button-only` is not set

props.name: closeButtonVariant
props.description: Button variant to use for the optional `close` button

props.name: disabled
props.description: Places the timepicker in a non-interactive disabled state

props.name: dropleft
props.description: When set, positions the menu to the left of the button

props.name: dropright
props.description: When set, positions the menu to the right of the button

props.name: dropup
props.description: When set, positions the menu on the top of the button

props.name: footerTag
props.description: Specify the HTML tag to render instead of the default tag for the footer

props.name: form
props.description: ID of the form that the form control belongs to. Sets the `form` attribute on the control

props.name: headerTag
props.description: Specify the HTML tag to render instead of the default tag for the header

props.name: hideHeader
props.description: When set, visually hides the selected time header

props.name: hour12
props.description: Tri-state prop. If `true` forces the interface to 12 hour format. If `false` forces the interface into 24 hour format. If `null` the current locale will determine the 12 or 24 hour interface (default)

props.name: labelAm
props.description: Text to display in the AM/PM spinbutton when 'AM' is selected

props.name: labelAmpm
props.description: Value of the `aria-label` attribute on the `AM/PM` spinbutton

props.name: labelCloseButton
props.description: Content for the `Close` button

props.name: labelDecrement
props.description: Value of the `aria-label` attribute on the spinbuttons `-` button

props.name: labelHours
props.description: Value of the `aria-label` attribute on the `Hours` spinbutton

props.name: labelIncrement
props.description: Value of the `aria-label` attribute on the spinbuttons `+` button

props.name: labelMinutes
props.description: Value of the `aria-label` attribute on the `Minutes` spinbutton

props.name: labelNoTimeSelected
props.description: String to show when no time is selected

props.name: labelNowButton
props.description: Content for the optional `Select now` button

props.name: labelPm
props.description: Text to display in the AM/PM spinbutton when 'PM' is selected

props.name: labelResetButton
props.description: Content for the optional `Reset` button

props.name: labelSeconds
props.description: Value of the `aria-label` attribute on the `Seconds` spinbutton

props.name: labelSelected
props.description: Hidden sr-only string when a time is selected

props.name: locale
props.description: Locale (or locales) for the component to use. When passing an array of locales, the order of the locales is from most preferred to least preferred. If not provided, defaults to the clients default locale

props.name: menuClass
props.description: Class (or classes) to apply to to popup menu wrapper

props.name: minutesStep
props.description: Step value for the minutes spinbutton. Should be a value evenly divided into 60

props.name: name
props.description: Sets the value of the `name` attribute on the form control

props.name: noCloseButton
props.description: When set, disables showing the close button

props.name: noFlip
props.description: Prevent the menu from auto flipping positions

props.name: nowButton
props.description: When set, shows the optional `select now` button

props.name: nowButtonVariant
props.description: Button variant to use for the optional `select today` button

props.name: offset
props.description: Specify the number of pixels to shift the menu by. Negative values supported

props.name: placeholder
props.description: Text so show in the form control when no date is selected. Defaults to the `label-no-date-selected` prop value

props.name: popperOpts
props.description: Additional configuration to pass to Popper.js

props.name: readonly
props.description: Places the timepicker in an interactive readonly state. Disables updating the v-model, while still allowing focusing of spin buttons

props.name: required
props.description: When set, adds the `aria-required="true"` attribute on the component. Required validation needs to be handled by your application

props.name: resetButton
props.description: When set, shows the optional `reset` button

props.name: resetButtonVariant
props.description: Button variant to use for the optional `reset` button

props.name: resetValue
props.description: When the optional `reset` button is clicked, the selected time will be set to this value. Default is to clear the selected value

props.name: right
props.description: Align the right edge of the menu with the right of the button

props.name: secondsStep
props.description: Step value for the seconds spinbutton. Should be a value evenly divided into 60

props.name: showSeconds
props.description: When true, shows the seconds spinbutton. If `false` the seconds spin button will not be shown and the seconds portion of the time will always be `0`

props.name: size
props.description: Set the size of the component's appearance. 'sm', 'md' (default), or 'lg'

props.name: state
props.description: Controls the validation state appearance of the component. `true` for valid, `false` for invalid, or `null` for no validation state

events.name: context
events.description: `b-time` context event. Emitted when the user changes any spinbutton value via mouse or cursor control. Also emitted when the component is first instantiated, or the locale is changed

arguments.name: context
arguments.description: The `b-time` context object. See the `b-time` documentaion for details

events.name: hidden
events.description: Emitted when the picker popup has hidden

events.name: input
events.description: Emitted when updating the v-model

arguments.name: time
arguments.description: A string in the format of `HH:mm:ss` (24 hour format)

events.name: shown
events.description: Emitted when the picker popup has shown

slots.name: button-content
slots.description: Content to place in the timepicker's icon button

vue-properties.name: hasFocus
vue-properties.description: `true` if the timepicker icon button has focus

vue-properties.name: isHovered
vue-properties.description: `true` if the component is hovered

vue-properties.name: open
vue-properties.description: The visibility state of the popup. `true` if the popup is visible and `false` if not

vue-properties.name: state
vue-properties.description: The value of the `state` prop. `true` (valid), `false` (invalid), or `null`

vue-components.description: Create responsive images, optionally adding lightweight styles to them  all via props. Support for rounded images, thumbnail styling, alignment, and even the ability to create blank images with an optional solid background color, and lazy loaded images.

props.description: Centers the image horizontally

props.description: Makes the image responsive. The image will shrink as needed or grow up the the image's native width

props.description: Similar to the 'fluid' prop, but allows the image to scale up past its native width

props.name: height
props.description: The value to set on the image's 'height' attribute

props.name: sizes
props.description: One or more strings separated by commas (or an array of strings), indicating a set of source sizes. Optionally used in combination with the srcset prop

props.name: src
props.description: URL to set for the `src` attribute

props.name: srcset
props.description: One or more strings separated by commas (or an array of strings), indicating possible image sources for the user agent to use

props.name: thumbnail
props.description: Adds a thumbnail border around the image

props.name: width
props.description: The value to set on the image's 'width' attribute

vue-components.name: BLink
vue-components.description: Use BootstrapVue's custom <b-link> component for generating a standard <a> link or <router-link>. <b-link> supports the disabled state and click event propagation.

props.name: active
props.description: When set to `true`, places the component in the active state with active styling

props.name: activeClass
props.description: <router-link> prop: Configure the active CSS class applied when the link is active. Typically you will want to set this to class name 'active'

props.name: append
props.description: <router-link> prop: Setting append prop always appends the relative path to the current path

props.name: disabled
props.description: When set to `true`, disables the component's functionality and places it in a disabled state

props.name: event
props.description: <router-link> prop: Specify the event that triggers the link. In most cases you should leave this as the default

props.name: exact
props.description: <router-link> prop: The default active class matching behavior is inclusive match. Setting this prop forces the mode to exactly match the route

props.name: exactActiveClass
props.description: <router-link> prop: Configure the active CSS class applied when the link is active with exact match. Typically you will want to set this to class name 'active'

props.name: exactPath
props.description: <router-link> prop: Allows matching only using the path section of the url, effectively ignoring the query and the hash sections

props.name: exactPathActiveClass
props.description: <router-link> prop: Configure the active CSS class applied when the link is active with exact path match. Typically you will want to set this to class name 'active'

props.name: href
props.description: Denotes the target URL of the link for standard a links

props.name: noPrefetch
props.description: <nuxt-link> prop: To improve the responsiveness of your Nuxt.js applications, when the link will be displayed within the viewport, Nuxt.js will automatically prefetch the code splitted page. Setting `no-prefetch` will disabled this feature for the specific link

props.name: prefetch
props.description: <nuxt-link> prop: To improve the responsiveness of your Nuxt.js applications, when the link will be displayed within the viewport, Nuxt.js will automatically prefetch the code splitted page. Setting `prefetch` to `true` or `false` will overwrite the default value of `router.prefetchLinks`

props.name: rel
props.description: Sets the 'rel' attribute on the rendered link

props.name: replace
props.description: <router-link> prop: Setting the replace prop will call `router.replace()` instead of `router.push()` when clicked, so the navigation will not leave a history record

props.name: routerComponentName
props.description: <b-link> prop: BootstrapVue auto detects between `<router-link>` and `<nuxt-link>`. In cases where you want to use a 3rd party link component based on `<router-link>`, set this prop to the component name. e.g. set it to 'g-link' if you are using Gridsome (note only `<router-link>` specific props are passed to the component)

props.name: routerTag
props.description: <router-link> prop: Specify which tag to render, and it will still listen to click events for navigation. `router-tag` translates to the tag prop on the final rendered `<router-link>`. Typically you should use the default value

props.name: target
props.description: Sets the 'target' attribute on the rendered link

props.name: to
props.description: <router-link> prop: Denotes the target route of the link. When clicked, the value of the to prop will be passed to `router.push()` internally, so the value can be either a string or a Location descriptor object

events.name: bv::link::clicked
events.description: Emitted on `$root` when link was clicked

arguments.name: mouseEvent
arguments.description: Native click event

events.name: click
events.description: Emitted when link was clicked

arguments.name: mouseEvent
arguments.description: Native click event

slots.name: default
slots.description: Content to place in the link

props.name: active

props.name: activeClass
props.description: <router-link> prop: Configure the active CSS class applied when the link is active. Typically you will want to set this to class name 'active'

props.name: append
props.description: <router-link> prop: Setting append prop always appends the relative path to the current path

props.name: disabled
props.description: When set to `true`, disables the component's functionality and places it in a disabled state

props.name: exact
props.description: <router-link> prop: The default active class matching behavior is inclusive match. Setting this prop forces the mode to exactly match the route

props.name: exactActiveClass
props.description: <router-link> prop: Configure the active CSS class applied when the link is active with exact match. Typically you will want to set this to class name 'active'

props.name: exactPath
props.description: <router-link> prop: Allows matching only using the path section of the url, effectively ignoring the query and the hash sections

props.name: exactPathActiveClass
props.description: <router-link> prop: Configure the active CSS class applied when the link is active with exact path match. Typically you will want to set this to class name 'active'

props.name: href
props.description: <b-link> prop: Denotes the target URL of the link for standard a links

props.name: linkAttrs
props.description: Additional attributes to place on the nested link element

props.name: linkClasses
props.description: CSS class (or classes) to place on the nested link element

props.name: noPrefetch
props.description: <nuxt-link> prop: To improve the responsiveness of your Nuxt.js applications, when the link will be displayed within the viewport, Nuxt.js will automatically prefetch the code splitted page. Setting `no-prefetch` will disabled this feature for the specific link

props.name: prefetch
props.description: <nuxt-link> prop: To improve the responsiveness of your Nuxt.js applications, when the link will be displayed within the viewport, Nuxt.js will automatically prefetch the code splitted page. Setting `prefetch` to `true` or `false` will overwrite the default value of `router.prefetchLinks`

props.name: rel

props.name: replace

props.name: routerComponentName

In cases where you want to use a 3rd party link component based on `<router-link>`, set this prop to the component name. e.g. set it to 'g-link' if you are using Gridsome (note only `<router-link>` specific props are passed to the component)

vue-components.name: BOverlay
vue-components.description: The b-overlay component is used to visually obscure a particular element or component and its content. It signals to the user of a state change within the element or component and can be used for creating loaders, warnings/alerts and more.

props.name: bgColor
props.description: CSS color to use as the opaque overlay backdrop color. If set, overrides the `variant` prop

props.name: blur
props.description: Value for the CSS blur backdrop-filter. Be sure to include the CSS units. Not supported in IE 11. Set to null or an empty string to disable blurring

props.name: fixed
props.description: When prop `no-wrap` is set, will use fixed positioning instead of absolute positioning. Handy if you want to obscure the entire application page

props.name: noCenter
props.description: When set, disables the vertical and horizontal centering of the overlay content

props.name: noFade
props.description: Disables the fade transition of the overlay

props.name: noWrap
props.description: Disabled generating the wrapper element, and ignored the default slot. Requires that `<b-overlay>` be placed in an element with position relative set

props.name: opacity
props.description: Opacity of the overlay backdrop. Valid range is `0` to `1`

props.name: overlayTag
props.description: Element tag to use as for the overlay element

props.name: rounded
props.description: Apply rounding to the overlay to match your content routing. Valid values are `true`, `'sm'`, `lg`, `circle`, `pill`, `top`, `right`, `bottom`, or `left`

props.name: show
props.description: When set, shows the overlay

props.name: spinnerSmall
props.description: When set, renders the default spinner in a smaller size

props.name: spinnerType
props.description: Type of the default spinner to show. Current supported types are 'border' and 'grow'

props.name: spinnerVariant
props.description: Applies one of the Bootstrap theme color variants to the default spinner. Default is to use the current font color

props.name: variant
props.description: Background theme color variant to use for the overlay backdrop

props.name: wrapTag
props.description: Element tag to use for the overall wrapper element. Has no effect if prop `no-wrap` is set

props.name: zIndex
props.description: Z-index value to apply to the overlay. You may need to increase this value to suit your content or placement

events.name: click
events.description: Emitted when overlay is clicked

arguments.name: event
arguments.description: Native click event object

events.name: hidden
events.description: Emitted when the overlay has been hidden

events.name: shown
events.description: Emitted when the overlay has been shown

slots.name: default
slots.description: The content to be overlayed. The default slot is ignored if the prop `no-wrap` is set

slots.name: overlay
slots.description: Custom content to replace the default overlay spinner

vue-components.name: BTable
vue-components.description: For displaying tabular data. <b-table> supports pagination, filtering, sorting, custom rendering, events, and asynchronous data. For simple display of tabular data without all the fancy features, BootstrapVue also provides lightweight alternative components <b-table-lite> and <b-table-simple>.

props.name: id
props.description: Used to set the `id` attribute on the rendered content, and used as the base to generate any additional element IDs as needed

props.name: value
props.description: Currently displayed row data. Read-only. Do not set a value on this prop

props.name: fields
props.description: Array of field names or array of field definition objects

props.name: items
props.description: Array of items to display, or an items provider function reference. Refer to the docs for details

props.name: primaryKey
props.description: Name of a table field that contains a guaranteed unique value per row. Needed for tbody transition support, and also speeds up table rendering

props.name: bordered
props.description: Adds borders to all the cells and headers

props.name: borderless
props.description: Removes all borders from cells

props.name: captionTop
props.description: Visually place the table caption above the table. Default is below

props.name: dark
props.description: Places the table in dark mode

props.name: fixed
props.description: Makes all columns equal width (fixed layout table). Will speed up rendering for large tables. Column widths can be set via CSS or colgroup

props.name: hover
props.description: Enables hover styling on rows

props.name: noBorderCollapse
props.description: Disable's the collapsing of table borders. Useful when table has sticky headers or columns

props.name: outlined
props.description: Adds an outline border to the table element

props.name: responsive
props.description: Makes the table responsive in width, adding a horizontal scrollbar. Set to true for always responsive or set to one of the breakpoints to switch from responsive to normal: 'sm', 'md', 'lg', 'xl'

props.name: small
props.description: Renders the table with smaller cell padding

props.name: stickyHeader
props.description: Makes the table header sticky. Set to true for a maximum height 300px tall table, or set to any valid CSS hight (including units)

props.name: striped
props.description: Applies striping to the tbody rows

props.name: tableClass
props.description: CSS class (or classes) to apply to the table element

props.name: tableVariant
props.description: Apply a Bootstrap theme color variant to the entire table

props.name: stacked
props.description: Place the table in stacked mode. Set to true for always stacked, or set to one of the breakpoints to switch from stacked to normal: 'sm', 'md', 'lg', 'xl'

props.name: headRowVariant
props.description: Apply a Bootstrap theme color variant to the tr element in the thead

props.name: headVariant
props.description: Header variant: 'light' or 'dark', or unset. May take precedence over head-row-variant

props.name: theadClass
props.description: CSS class (or classes) to apply to the thead element

props.name: theadTrClass
props.description: CSS class (or classes) to apply to the tr element in the thead

props.name: footClone
props.description: Enable the footer of the table, and clone the header content by default

props.name: footRowVariant
props.description: Apply a Bootstrap theme color variant to the tr element in the tfoot. Falls back to head-row-variant

props.name: footVariant
props.description: Footer variant: 'light' or 'dark', or unset. May take precedence over foot-row-variant

props.name: tfootClass
props.description: CSS class (or classes) to apply to the tfoot element

props.name: tfootTrClass
props.description: CSS class (or classes) to apply to the tr element in the tfoot

props.name: detailsTdClass
props.description: CSS class (or classes) to apply to the row details' `td` element for the row-details slot

props.name: tbodyTrAttr
props.description: Attributes to be added to each tr in the tbody, or a function returning such attributes (see docs for details)

props.name: tbodyTrClass
props.description: CSS class (or classes) to apply to the tr element in the tbody. Can be a function that returns a class (see docs for details)

props.name: tbodyClass
props.description: CSS class (or classes) to apply to the tbody element

props.name: tbodyTransitionHandlers
props.description: Vue 'transition-group' event handlers. When provided will make the tbody a Vue 'transition-group' component

props.name: tbodyTransitionProps
props.description: Vue 'transition-group' properties. When provided will make the tbody a Vue 'transition-group' component

props.name: filter
props.description: Criteria for filtering. Internal filtering supports only string or RegExpr criteria

props.name: filterDebounce
props.description: Time in milliseconds to debounce changes to the filter criteria before filtering the records

props.name: filterFunction
props.description: Reference to a function to use instead of the internal filtering function. Refer to the docs for details

props.name: filterIgnoredFields
props.description: Array of top level fields to ignore when filtering the item data

props.name: filterIncludedFields
props.description: Array of fields to include when filtering. Overrides filter-ignore-fields

props.name: labelSortAsc
props.description: Hidden string to place in the header cell when clicking the cell will change the sort direction to ascending

props.name: labelSortClear
props.description: Hidden string to place in the header cell when clicking the cell will clear the current sorting direction

props.name: labelSortDesc
props.description: Hidden string to place in the header cell when clicking the cell will change the sort direction to descending

props.name: noFooterSorting
props.description: When the build in formatter is used, setting this prop will disable the sorting ability in the footer

props.name: noLocalSorting
props.description: Disabled the internal sorting routine, and expects the user to provde the items sorted. Sorting controls will still be available

props.name: noSortReset
props.description: When a table is sortable, clicking on any non-sortable column heading will clear the current sort values. Set this prop to disable this feature

props.name: sortBy
props.description: Field name that is currently being sorted. Set to null to clear sorting. Syncable with the .sync prop modifier

props.name: sortCompare
props.description: A reference to a function for sort-comparing two rows of data. Defaults to the internal sort compare routine. See docs for details

props.name: sortCompareLocale
props.description: The locale string (or array of locale string) that specified the language when sorting. See docs for details

props.name: sortCompareOptions
props.description: An object containing sort configuration for the 'String.prototype.sortLocale' method. See docs for details

props.name: sortDesc
props.description: Set to true to sort the column in descending order. Syncable with the .sync prop modifier

props.name: sortDirection
props.description: The initial sorting direction to sort an unsorted column by: 'asc', 'desc', or 'last' (to use the previous sort direction)

props.name: sortIconLeft
props.description: Positions the sort control to the left of the header text. Default is on the right of the header text

props.name: sortNullLast
props.description: When sorting, null and undefined values will be sorted first (or last, depending on 'sort-desc'). Set this prop to sort null values last. Only applicable to internal sorting

props.name: currentPage
props.description: The current page number to display when the table is paginated. Starting from 1 and up

props.name: perPage
props.description: Number of rows to show per page. Set to 0 to disable pagination

props.name: caption
props.description: Text string to place in the caption element

props.name: captionHtml
props.description: HTML string to place in the caption element

props.name: noSelectOnClick
props.description: Disables row selection via click events. Row selection will be only available programmatically

props.name: selectMode
props.description: The selectable mode for the table when 'selectable' is set. Possible values: 'single', 'multi' or 'range'

props.name: selectable
props.description: When set, places the table body rows in selectable mode

props.name: selectedVariant
props.description: Bootstrap color theme variant to set selected rows to. Use any of the standard Bootstrap theme color variants, or the special table row variant 'active' (default). Set to an empty string to not use a variant

props.name: emptyFilteredHtml
props.description: HTML string to show when the table has no items to show due to filtering

props.name: emptyFilteredText
props.default: "There are no records matching your request"
props.description: Text string to show when the table has no items to show due to filtering

props.name: emptyHtml
props.description: HTML string to show when the table has no items to show

props.name: emptyText
props.description: Text string to show when the table has no items to show

props.name: showEmpty
props.description: When enabled, and there are no item records to show, shows a message that there are no rows to show

props.name: busy
props.description: When set, forces the table into the busy state.Automatically set when an items provider function is being called

props.name: apiUrl
props.description: Pass through prop. Passed as part of the context object sent to the items provider function

props.name: noProviderFiltering
props.description: When set, uses internal filtering to pagination the data. Otherwise the provider is expected to perform the filtering

props.name: noProviderPaging
props.description: When set, uses internal paging to pagination the data. Otherwise the items provider is expected to perform the paging

props.name: noProviderSorting
props.description: When set, uses internal sorting to sort the data. Otherwise the items provider is expected to perform the sorting

vue-components.description: Bootstrap Icons are designed to work with Bootstrap components, from form controls to navigation. Bootstrap Icons are SVGs, so they scale quickly and easily and can be styled with CSS.

props.name: animation
props.description: Animate the icon. Supported built-in animations are 'cylon', 'fade', 'pulse', 'spin' and 'throb'

props.name: flipH
props.description: Flips the icon horizontally

props.name: flipV
props.description: Flips the icon vertically

props.name: fontScale
props.description: Scale the icons current font size

props.name: icon
props.description: Name of icon to render. The corresponding icon component must be installed

props.name: rotate
props.description: Rotates the icon by the specified number of degrees. Positive values rotate clockwise, while negative values rotate counterclockwise

props.name: scale
props.description: Scales the icon's SVG, without increasing the font size

props.name: shiftH
props.description: Moves the icon horizontally. Positive numbers will shift the icon right, negative left. Value is in 1/16em units

props.name: shiftV
props.description: Moves the icon vertically. Positive numbers will shift the icon up, negative down. Value is in 1/16em units

props.name: stacked
props.description: Set this prop to true when placing inside a BIconstack component

props.name: title
props.description: Text content to place in the title

props.name: variant
props.description: Contextual color variant. By default the icon inherits the current text color

vue-directives.name: b-modal
vue-directives.description: Modals are streamlined, but flexible dialog prompts powered by JavaScript and CSS. They support a number of use cases from user notification to completely custom content and feature a handful of helpful sub-components, sizes, variants, accessibility, and more.

modifiers.name: {modalId}
modifiers.description: Modal ID to open. Replace `{modalId}` with the modal's ID

vue-directives.name: b-hover
vue-directives.description: A lightweight directive that allows you to react when an element either becomes hovered or unhovered

vue-directives.name: b-popover
vue-directives.description: Add BootstrapVue popovers to any element on your site, using Bootstrap v4 CSS for styling and animations. Popovers are tooltips on steroids.

argument.description: ID of element to append the popover markup when visible. Optional, defaults to the body

modifiers.name: top
modifiers.description: Positions the popover on the top of the trigger element (default)

modifiers.name: right
modifiers.description: Positions the popover on the right of the trigger element

modifiers.name: bottom
modifiers.description: Positions the popover on the bottom of the trigger element

modifiers.name: auto
modifiers.description: Positions the popover in the best fit place around the trigger element

modifiers.name: topright
modifiers.description: Positions the popover on the top-right of the trigger element

modifiers.name: topleft
modifiers.description: Positions the popover on the top-left of the trigger element

modifiers.name: bottomright
modifiers.description: Positions the popover on the bottom-right of the trigger element

modifiers.name: bottomleft
modifiers.description: Positions the popover on the bottom-left of the trigger element

modifiers.name: lefttop
modifiers.description: Positions the popover on the left-top of the trigger element

modifiers.name: leftbottom
modifiers.description: Positions the popover on the left-bottom of the trigger element

modifiers.name: righttop
modifiers.description: Positions the popover on the right-top of the trigger element

modifiers.name: rightbottom
modifiers.description: Positions the popover on the right-bottom of the trigger element

modifiers.name: nofade
modifiers.description: Disabled the fade animation of the popover

modifiers.name: html
modifiers.description: Enables basic HTML in the title/content

modifiers.name: viewport
modifiers.description: Sets the boundary constraint to the viewport

modifiers.name: window
modifiers.description: Sets the boundary constrain to the window

modifiers.name: v-{variant}
modifiers.description: Sets the popover contextual color variant to `{variant}`

modifiers.name: d{###}
modifiers.description: The show and hide delay in milliseconds (where `{###}` is the value in milliseconds)

modifiers.name: ds{###}
modifiers.description: The show delay in milliseconds (where `{###}` is the value in milliseconds)

modifiers.name: dh{###}
modifiers.description: The hide delay in milliseconds (where `{###}` is the value in milliseconds)

modifiers.name: o{###}
modifiers.description: An offset value in pixels (where `{###}` is the number of pixels, defaults to 0. Negative values allowed)

vue-directives.name: b-scrollspy
vue-directives.description: Automatically activate BootstrapVue navigation or list group components based on scroll position to indicate which link is currently active in the viewport.

argument.description: ID of element to monitor scrolling on (if not provided defaults to the body element)

modifiers.description: Offset (in pixels) from top of scrolling viewport before triggering active state

modifiers.name: offset
modifiers.description: Position calculation method using `offset` procedure (default process for body)

modifiers.name: position
modifiers.description: Position calculation method using the `position` procedure

modifiers.name: auto
modifiers.description: Position calculation method: `auto` will choose `offset` if scroll element is body, else the method is `position`. This is the default

vue-directives.name: b-toggle
vue-directives.description: A light-weight directive for toggling visibility state for collapses and sidebars by ID. It automatically handles the accessibility attributes on the trigger element.

modifiers.name: {componentId}
modifiers.description: ID of component to toggle

vue-directives.description: The `v-b-visible` directive allows you to react when an element becomes visible in the viewport.
